  <h2>Where is the Reference Number on Your Bill?</h2>
    <p>On every WAPDA DISCO electricity bill, the 14-digit reference number is printed in <strong>bold on the top-right section</strong> of the bill. It is usually labeled <strong>"Reference No."</strong> or <strong>"Ref. No."</strong> and appears directly above or below the barcode. It is always exactly 14 digits — no letters, no dashes.</p>

    <div style="background:#f0fdf4;border-left:4px solid #01411C;padding:1rem 1.5rem;border-radius:8px;margin:1.5rem 0;">
      <strong>Quick Visual Guide:</strong> Look at the TOP section of your bill → RIGHT side → find the 14-digit number → that is your reference number.
    </div>

