    <h2>What if I Can't Find My Reference Number?</h2>
    <p>If you've lost your paper bill and cannot find your reference number, you have several options:</p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li><strong>Check previous months' bills</strong> — the reference number never changes for your connection</li>
      <li><strong>Call your DISCO helpline (118)</strong> — provide your name, address, and CNIC to retrieve your reference number</li>
      <li><strong>Visit your nearest subdivision office</strong> — with your CNIC for identity verification</li>
      <li><strong>Use your Customer ID (10 digits)</strong> — all DISCO bill checkers also accept the 10-digit Customer ID as an alternative</li>
      <li><strong>Check your bank payment records</strong> — if you've paid bills online, your reference number is saved in payment history</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Reference Number vs Customer ID — What's the Difference?</h2>
    <p>Both numbers identify your electricity connection, but they are used differently:</p>
    <ul style="padding-left:1.5rem;line-height:2.2;">
      <li><strong>Reference Number (14 digits)</strong> — used for bill checking and payment. May change if your connection moves to a new feeder. Most apps and SMS services use this.</li>
      <li><strong>Customer ID / Consumer No. (10 digits)</strong> — your permanent account identifier. Never changes. Used for new connection applications and DISCO records.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Our bill checkers at PakistanBill.online accept both — just click the appropriate tab on any bill checker page.</p>

